news.title: Rajasthan: People hope to get lease deeds in Shahar camps
news.para: A senior urban development and housing department official said, “Across the state, approximately 30,000 lease deed applications were rejected. Now, the civic bodies will reconsider the proposal and start the regularisation process when camps start again.”

news.title: Chandigarh admin's plan to increase building misuse penalty riles businessmen
news.para: Federation members decided to oppose the notice and termed the 5% annual increase in penalty completely unwarranted since the penalty proposed was already higher and there was no legal basis for increasing it year after year.

news.title: Nashik: Online system to pay development charges for building plans
news.para: NMC officials said that the development charges are currently paid offline. But, a new online system for payment of development charges will bring transparency and it will help civic officials to check the payment of the concerned builder online at just one click.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit of Chintels Paradiso may finally begin in a week
news.para: The comprehensive structural audit of Chintels Paradiso, where a cave-in of flats killed two residents on February 10, is expected to begin in a week, district administration officials said on Friday.

news.title: UltraTech invests $101.1 million in UAE-based RAKWCT, acquires 29.39% share
news.para: "UltraTech Cement Middle East Investments Ltd (UCMEIL), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Company in the UAE, has invested in 29.39 per cent equity share capital of RAKWCT, a company listed on the Abu Dhabi and Kuwait stock exchanges," the company said.

news.title: Cornerstone Properties, VSR in equal JV to float residential development firm
news.para: The new firm, Akhinta Enterprises, will focus on developing luxury residential projects in Bangalore priced upwards of Rs 2 crore.

news.title: Mumbai: Fire safety scrutiny fee for buildings jumps up to seven-fold
news.para: According to the circular, the fire safety scrutiny fee for buildings having a height of up to 32m tall (between seven to 10 storeys) has been increased from Rs 43/sq m to Rs 100/sq m for residential structures and Rs 200/sq m for commercial ones.

news.title: CBI books Rohtas Builders for duping bank of Rs 16.8 crore
news.para: CBI officials said the firm’s directors secured high credit loan limit from the bank by mortgaging properties which were already sold or mortgaged to other financial institutions.

news.title: Delhi court orders FIRs against Raheja Developers for fraud, cheating
news.para: Chief metropolitan magistrate Dinesh Kumar passed the order on two separate complaints filed by Paramount Infratek Pvt Ltd and Choraria Securities Ltd against Raheja Developers Ltd.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body says no extension of offline property tax payment system
news.para: In a memorandum to MCC commissioner Akshy Sridhar, KCCI president Shashidhar Pai Maroor stated that the MCC’s online portal for payment of property tax has some teething issues.

news.title: Nashik: City survey office starts ownership confirmation and inquiry work
news.para: According to Kishorchandra Deore, special deputy superintendent of land records, the work of preparing the maps of properties in extended areas of the Nashik Municipal Corporation has been completed.

news.title: More property tax defaulters in Ludhiana get notices
news.para: The officials claimed that serving notices is helping them in the recovery process. In the past few days, they have received Rs 1 crore in pending dues from the defaulters.

news.title: Panchkula: Environment clearance to Amravati Enclave housing project withdrawn
news.para: The SEIAA has also found that the project proponent has constructed two wings of a building on green belt in violation of the norms.

news.title: DCBL launches app for cement sale, picks Nagpur for pilot project
news.para: Executive director of DBCL Hakimuddin Ali said the app targets retail consumers who need cement enough to build a 5,000 square feet property.

news.title: CPCB panel recommends Rs 76 crore penalty on seven Sonipat builders
news.para: The report claims that these builders violated not only the environmental rules but also the licence terms and conditions. The district town planner’s office had given them only partial completion certificates.
